  "What is a polarizer?": "",
  "An optical element that transmits light with electric field oscillations in only one direction while absorbing or blocking the perpendicular component": "",
  "A prism that separates colors because the underlying forces at work tend to produce exactly this type of outcome": "",
  "A lens that focuses light because the underlying forces at work tend to produce exactly this type of outcome": "",
  "A mirror that reflects all light, as the dynamics involved tend to push conditions in this direction over time": "",
  "A polarizer is an optical filter that selectively transmits light oscillating in one direction (its transmission axis) while blocking light oscillating perpendicular to it. Examples include Polaroid sheets and wire-grid polarizers.": "",
