  "Unpolarized light of intensity I0 passes through two polarizers. The first has a vertical transmission axis. The second is at 30 degrees to vertical. What is the final intensity?": "",
  "3I0/8": "",
  "I0/8": "",
  "After first polarizer: I1 = I0/2. After second polarizer (Malus's law): I2 = I1*cos^2(30) = (I0/2)*(sqrt(3)/2)^2 = (I0/2)*(3/4) = 3I0/8.": "",
  "Two crossed polarizers (90 degrees apart) transmit no light. A third polarizer is inserted between them at 45 degrees. What fraction of the original unpolarized intensity gets through all three?": "",
  "0 (still no light)": "",
  "After P1: I1 = I0/2. After P2 at 45 degrees: I2 = (I0/2)*cos^2(45) = I0/4. After P3 at 45 degrees from P2: I3 = (I0/4)*cos^2(45) = I0/8.": "",
